11/04/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The tripartite BiH presidency and Turkish President Ahmet Necdet Sezer reaffirmed their mutual will for bilateral collaboration and EU integration, during a meeting Monday (10 April) in Sarajevo. Acknowledging the two countries' "deep historic roots and strong cultural connection", Sezer said that Ankara fully backs BiH's aspirations for NATO accession, as well as the EU Stabilisation and Association Process. 
In other news Monday, relatives of Sarajevo Serbs missing since the BiH conflict gathered to protest in front of the Federation of BiH (FBiH) government, demanding information. The demonstrators denounced the failure of FBiH Prime Minister Ahmet Hadzipasic to form a truth commission regarding the missing, as promised. (Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 11/04/06; Fena, PBS BiH, NTV Hayat, RTRS - 10/04/06)
